A 'Cylindropuntia ramosissima' is a species of cactus found in the southwestern United States and northern Mexico. 
It is known for its branching structure and cylindrical stem segments. 
The stem segments are green in color with sharp spines protruding from them. 
The spines can range in color from yellow to brown. 
The plant produces small, yellowish-green flowers that bloom from late spring to early summer. 
It is often found in dry, arid environments such as deserts, rocky slopes, and canyons. 
The plant is sometimes used for landscaping purposes or in horticulture.
